FBIS4-14705 "drsov064_s_94013" FBIS-SOV-94-064 Daily Report 4 Apr 1994 Georgia Attack on Border Villages Launched Attack on Border Villages Launched LD0404084794 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0704 GMT 4 Apr 94 LD0404084794 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network Georgian BFN [Text] The Defense Ministry press service reports that Abkhaz separatists have shelled Koki, a village on the left bank of the Enguri river, from a tank, and also launched an attack on Georgian positions near Khurcha. The attack, which was preceded by artillery shelling, was carried out by a large enemy unit using a tank and three APC's. The enemy was repelled by Defense Ministry units. There are no victims on our side. A dam at the Enguri hydroelectric power station was damaged yesterday, Electricity supplies to Zugdidi rayon have now been restored, however.
